<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-19-0431 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper concerns the anthropic Universe. The author argues that thereis something special about the time and place that has produced intelligentlife. Basic constants of nature, and the combination of them to obtaincertain dimensionless ratios, are examined with respect to their significance.Apparent coincidences involving basic physical laws and ratios, wherea rather delicate balance often seems to prevail, are also discussed.(U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>